98AccessibilityObject::~AccessibilityObject()
99{
100 ASSERT(isDetached());
101}
102
103void AccessibilityObject::detachRemoteParts(AccessibilityDetachmentType detachmentType)
104{
105 // Menu close events need to notify the platform. No element is used in the notification because it's a destruction event.
106 if (detachmentType == AccessibilityDetachmentType::ElementDestroyed && roleValue() == AccessibilityRole::Menu) {
107 if (auto* cache = axObjectCache())
108 cache->postNotification(nullptr, &cache->document(), AXObjectCache::AXMenuClosed);
109 }
110
111 // Clear any children and call detachFromParent on them so that
112 // no children are left with dangling pointers to their parent.
113 clearChildren();
114}

116bool AccessibilityObject::isDetached() const
117{
118#if ENABLE(ACCESSIBILITY)
119 return !wrapper();
120#else
121 return true;
122#endif
123}

125// ARIA marks elements as having their accessible name derive from either their contents, or their author provide name.
126bool AccessibilityObject::accessibleNameDerivesFromContent() const
127{
128 // First check for objects specifically identified by ARIA.
129 switch (ariaRoleAttribute()) {
130 case AccessibilityRole::ApplicationAlert:
131 case AccessibilityRole::ApplicationAlertDialog:
132 case AccessibilityRole::ApplicationDialog:
133 case AccessibilityRole::ApplicationGroup:
134 case AccessibilityRole::ApplicationLog:
135 case AccessibilityRole::ApplicationMarquee:
136 case AccessibilityRole::ApplicationStatus:
137 case AccessibilityRole::ApplicationTimer:
138 case AccessibilityRole::ComboBox:
139 case AccessibilityRole::Definition:
140 case AccessibilityRole::Document:
141 case AccessibilityRole::DocumentArticle:
142 case AccessibilityRole::DocumentMath:
143 case AccessibilityRole::DocumentNote:
144 case AccessibilityRole::LandmarkRegion:
145 case AccessibilityRole::LandmarkDocRegion:
146 case AccessibilityRole::Form:
147 case AccessibilityRole::Grid:
148 case AccessibilityRole::Group:
149 case AccessibilityRole::Image:
150 case AccessibilityRole::List:
151 case AccessibilityRole::ListBox:
152 case AccessibilityRole::LandmarkBanner:
153 case AccessibilityRole::LandmarkComplementary:
154 case AccessibilityRole::LandmarkContentInfo:
155 case AccessibilityRole::LandmarkNavigation:
156 case AccessibilityRole::LandmarkMain:
157 case AccessibilityRole::LandmarkSearch:
158 case AccessibilityRole::Menu:
159 case AccessibilityRole::MenuBar:
160 case AccessibilityRole::ProgressIndicator:
161 case AccessibilityRole::Meter:
162 case AccessibilityRole::RadioGroup:
163 case AccessibilityRole::ScrollBar:
164 case AccessibilityRole::Slider:
165 case AccessibilityRole::SpinButton:
166 case AccessibilityRole::Splitter:
167 case AccessibilityRole::Table:
168 case AccessibilityRole::TabList:
169 case AccessibilityRole::TabPanel:
170 case AccessibilityRole::TextArea:
171 case AccessibilityRole::TextField:
172 case AccessibilityRole::Toolbar:
173 case AccessibilityRole::TreeGrid:
174 case AccessibilityRole::Tree:
175 case AccessibilityRole::WebApplication:
176 return false;
177 default:
178 break;
179 }
180
181 // Now check for generically derived elements now that we know the element does not match a specific ARIA role.
182 switch (roleValue()) {
183 case AccessibilityRole::Slider:
184 case AccessibilityRole::ListBox:
185 return false;
186 default:
187 break;
188 }
189
190 return true;
191}

193String AccessibilityObject::computedLabel()
194{
195 // This method is being called by WebKit inspector, which may happen at any time, so we need to update our backing store now.
196 // Also hold onto this object in case updateBackingStore deletes this node.
197 RefPtr<AccessibilityObject> protectedThis(this);
198 updateBackingStore();
199 Vector<AccessibilityText> text;
200 accessibilityText(text);
201 if (text.size())
202 return text[0].text;
203 return String();
204}

246bool AccessibilityObject::hasMisspelling() const
247{
248 if (!node())
249 return false;
250
251 Frame* frame = node()->document().frame();
252 if (!frame)
253 return false;
254
255 Editor& editor = frame->editor();
256
257 TextCheckerClient* textChecker = editor.textChecker();
258 if (!textChecker)
259 return false;
260
261 bool isMisspelled = false;
262
263 if (unifiedTextCheckerEnabled(frame)) {
264 Vector<TextCheckingResult> results;
265 checkTextOfParagraph(*textChecker, stringValue(), TextCheckingType::Spelling, results, frame->selection().selection());
266 if (!results.isEmpty())
267 isMisspelled = true;
268 return isMisspelled;
269 }
270
271 int misspellingLength = 0;
272 int misspellingLocation = -1;
273 textChecker->checkSpellingOfString(stringValue(), &misspellingLocation, &misspellingLength);
274 if (misspellingLength || misspellingLocation != -1)
275 isMisspelled = true;
276
277 return isMisspelled;
278}

280std::optional<SimpleRange> AccessibilityObject::misspellingRange(const SimpleRange& start, AccessibilitySearchDirection direction) const
281{
282 auto node = this->node();
283 if (!node)
284 return std::nullopt;
285
286 Frame* frame = node->document().frame();
287 if (!frame)
288 return std::nullopt;
289
290 if (!unifiedTextCheckerEnabled(frame))
291 return std::nullopt;
292
293 Editor& editor = frame->editor();
294
295 TextCheckerClient* textChecker = editor.textChecker();
296 if (!textChecker)
297 return std::nullopt;
298
299 Vector<TextCheckingResult> misspellings;
300 checkTextOfParagraph(*textChecker, stringValue(), TextCheckingType::Spelling, misspellings, frame->selection().selection());
301
302 // Find the first misspelling past the start.
303 if (direction == AccessibilitySearchDirection::Next) {
304 for (auto& misspelling : misspellings) {
305 auto misspellingRange = editor.rangeForTextCheckingResult(misspelling);
306 if (misspellingRange && is_gt(treeOrder<ComposedTree>(misspellingRange->end, start.end)))
307 return *misspellingRange;
308 }
309 } else {
310 for (auto& misspelling : makeReversedRange(misspellings)) {
311 auto misspellingRange = editor.rangeForTextCheckingResult(misspelling);
312 if (misspellingRange && is_lt(treeOrder<ComposedTree>(misspellingRange->start, start.start)))
313 return *misspellingRange;
314 }
315 }
316
317 return std::nullopt;
318}

320unsigned AccessibilityObject::blockquoteLevel() const
321{
322 unsigned level = 0;
323 for (Node* elementNode = node(); elementNode; elementNode = elementNode->parentNode()) {
324 if (elementNode->hasTagName(blockquoteTag))
325 ++level;
326 }
327
328 return level;
329}

338AccessibilityObject* AccessibilityObject::previousSiblingUnignored(int limit) const
339{
340 AccessibilityObject* previous;
341 ASSERT(limit >= 0);
342 for (previous = previousSibling(); previous && previous->accessibilityIsIgnored(); previous = previous->previousSibling()) {
343 limit--;
344 if (limit <= 0)
345 break;
346 }
347 return previous;
348}

350FloatRect AccessibilityObject::convertFrameToSpace(const FloatRect& frameRect, AccessibilityConversionSpace conversionSpace) const
351{
352 ASSERT(isMainThread());
353
354 // Find the appropriate scroll view to use to convert the contents to the window.
355 const auto parentAccessibilityScrollView = ancestorAccessibilityScrollView(false /* includeSelf */);
356 auto* parentScrollView = parentAccessibilityScrollView ? parentAccessibilityScrollView->scrollView() : nullptr;
357
358 auto snappedFrameRect = snappedIntRect(IntRect(frameRect));
359 if (parentScrollView)
360 snappedFrameRect = parentScrollView->contentsToRootView(snappedFrameRect);
361
362 if (conversionSpace == AccessibilityConversionSpace::Screen) {
363 auto page = this->page();
364 if (!page)
365 return snappedFrameRect;
366
367 // If we have an empty chrome client (like SVG) then we should use the page
368 // of the scroll view parent to help us get to the screen rect.
369 if (parentAccessibilityScrollView && page->chrome().client().isEmptyChromeClient())
370 page = parentAccessibilityScrollView->page();
371
372 snappedFrameRect = page->chrome().rootViewToAccessibilityScreen(snappedFrameRect);
373 }
374
375 return snappedFrameRect;
376}
377
378FloatRect AccessibilityObject::relativeFrame() const
379{
380 return convertFrameToSpace(elementRect(), AccessibilityConversionSpace::Page);
381}

401
402AccessibilityObject* firstAccessibleObjectFromNode(const Node* node, const WTF::Function<bool(const AccessibilityObject&)>& isAccessible)
403{
404 if (!node)
405 return nullptr;
406
407 AXObjectCache* cache = node->document().axObjectCache();
408 if (!cache)
409 return nullptr;
410
411 AccessibilityObject* accessibleObject = cache->getOrCreate(node->renderer());
412 while (accessibleObject && !isAccessible(*accessibleObject)) {
413 node = NodeTraversal::next(*node);
414
415 while (node && !node->renderer())
416 node = NodeTraversal::nextSkippingChildren(*node);
417
418 if (!node)
419 return nullptr;
420
421 accessibleObject = cache->getOrCreate(node->renderer());
422 }
423
424 return accessibleObject;
425}

434static void appendAccessibilityObject(AXCoreObject* object, AccessibilityObject::AccessibilityChildrenVector& results)
435{
436 // Find the next descendant of this attachment object so search can continue through frames.
437 if (object->isAttachment()) {
438 Widget* widget = object->widgetForAttachmentView();
439 if (!is<FrameView>(widget))
440 return;
441
442 Document* document = downcast<FrameView>(*widget).frame().document();
443 if (!document || !document->hasLivingRenderTree())
444 return;
445
446 object = object->axObjectCache()->getOrCreate(document);
447 }
448
449 if (object)
450 results.append(object);
451}
452
453void AccessibilityObject::insertChild(AXCoreObject* child, unsigned index)
454{
455 if (!child)
456 return;
457
458 // If the parent is asking for this child's children, then either it's the first time (and clearing is a no-op),
459 // or its visibility has changed. In the latter case, this child may have a stale child cached.
460 // This can prevent aria-hidden changes from working correctly. Hence, whenever a parent is getting children, ensure data is not stale.
461 // Only clear the child's children when we know it's in the updating chain in order to avoid unnecessary work.
462 if (child->needsToUpdateChildren() || m_subtreeDirty) {
463 child->clearChildren();
464 // Pass m_subtreeDirty flag down to the child so that children cache gets reset properly.
465 if (m_subtreeDirty)
466 child->setNeedsToUpdateSubtree();
467 } else {
468 // For some reason the grand children might be detached so that we need to regenerate the
469 // children list of this child.
470 for (const auto& grandChild : child->children(false)) {
471 if (grandChild->isDetachedFromParent()) {
472 child->clearChildren();
473 break;
474 }
475 }
476 }
477
478 setIsIgnoredFromParentDataForChild(child);
479 if (child->accessibilityIsIgnored()) {
480 const auto& children = child->children();
481 size_t length = children.size();
482 for (size_t i = 0; i < length; ++i)
483 m_children.insert(index + i, children[i]);
484 } else {
485 ASSERT(child->parentObject() == this);
486 m_children.insert(index, child);
487 }
488
489 // Reset the child's m_isIgnoredFromParentData since we are done adding that child and its children.
490 child->clearIsIgnoredFromParentData();
491}
492
493void AccessibilityObject::addChild(AXCoreObject* child)
494{
495 insertChild(child, m_children.size());
496}

498void AccessibilityObject::findMatchingObjects(AccessibilitySearchCriteria* criteria, AccessibilityChildrenVector& results)
499{
500 ASSERT(criteria);
501 if (!criteria)
502 return;
503
504 if (AXObjectCache* cache = axObjectCache())
505 cache->startCachingComputedObjectAttributesUntilTreeMutates();
506
507 criteria->anchorObject = this;
508 Accessibility::findMatchingObjects(*criteria, results);
509}

511// Returns the range that is fewer positions away from the reference range.
512// NOTE: The after range is expected to ACTUALLY be after the reference range and the before
513// range is expected to ACTUALLY be before. These are not checked for performance reasons.
514static std::optional<SimpleRange> rangeClosestToRange(const SimpleRange& referenceRange, std::optional<SimpleRange>&& afterRange, std::optional<SimpleRange>&& beforeRange)
515{
516 if (!beforeRange)
517 return WTFMove(afterRange);
518 if (!afterRange)
519 return WTFMove(beforeRange);
520 auto distanceBefore = characterCount({ beforeRange->end, referenceRange.start });
521 auto distanceAfter = characterCount({ afterRange->start, referenceRange.end });
522 return WTFMove(distanceBefore <= distanceAfter ? beforeRange : afterRange);
523}
524
525std::optional<SimpleRange> AccessibilityObject::rangeOfStringClosestToRangeInDirection(const SimpleRange& referenceRange, AccessibilitySearchDirection searchDirection, const Vector<String>& searchStrings) const
526{
527 Frame* frame = this->frame();
528 if (!frame)
529 return std::nullopt;
530
531 bool isBackwardSearch = searchDirection == AccessibilitySearchDirection::Previous;
532 FindOptions findOptions { AtWordStarts, AtWordEnds, CaseInsensitive, StartInSelection };
533 if (isBackwardSearch)
534 findOptions.add(FindOptionFlag::Backwards);
535
536 std::optional<SimpleRange> closestStringRange;
537 for (auto& searchString : searchStrings) {
538 if (auto foundStringRange = frame->editor().rangeOfString(searchString, referenceRange, findOptions)) {
539 bool foundStringIsCloser;
540 if (!closestStringRange)
541 foundStringIsCloser = true;
542 else {
543 foundStringIsCloser = isBackwardSearch
544 ? is_gt(treeOrder<ComposedTree>(foundStringRange->end, closestStringRange->end))
545 : is_lt(treeOrder<ComposedTree>(foundStringRange->start, closestStringRange->start));
546 }
547 if (foundStringIsCloser)
548 closestStringRange = *foundStringRange;
549 }
550 }
551 return closestStringRange;
552}

554// Returns an collapsed range preceding the document contents if there is no selection.
555// FIXME: Why is that behavior more useful than returning null in that case?
556std::optional<SimpleRange> AccessibilityObject::selectionRange() const
557{
558 auto frame = this->frame();
559 if (!frame)
560 return std::nullopt;
561
562 if (auto range = frame->selection().selection().firstRange())
563 return *range;
564
565 auto& document = *frame->document();
566 return { { { document, 0 }, { document, 0 } } };
567}

577std::optional<SimpleRange> AccessibilityObject::findTextRange(const Vector<String>& searchStrings, const SimpleRange& start, AccessibilitySearchTextDirection direction) const
578{
579 std::optional<SimpleRange> found;
580 if (direction == AccessibilitySearchTextDirection::Forward)
581 found = rangeOfStringClosestToRangeInDirection(start, AccessibilitySearchDirection::Next, searchStrings);
582 else if (direction == AccessibilitySearchTextDirection::Backward)
583 found = rangeOfStringClosestToRangeInDirection(start, AccessibilitySearchDirection::Previous, searchStrings);
584 else if (direction == AccessibilitySearchTextDirection::Closest) {
585 auto foundAfter = rangeOfStringClosestToRangeInDirection(start, AccessibilitySearchDirection::Next, searchStrings);
586 auto foundBefore = rangeOfStringClosestToRangeInDirection(start, AccessibilitySearchDirection::Previous, searchStrings);
587 found = rangeClosestToRange(start, WTFMove(foundAfter), WTFMove(foundBefore));
588 }
589 if (found) {
590 // If the search started within a text control, ensure that the result is inside that element.
591 if (element() && element()->isTextField()) {
592 if (!found->startContainer().isDescendantOrShadowDescendantOf(element())
593 || !found->endContainer().isDescendantOrShadowDescendantOf(element()))
594 return std::nullopt;
595 }
596 }
597 return found;
598}
599
600Vector<SimpleRange> AccessibilityObject::findTextRanges(const AccessibilitySearchTextCriteria& criteria) const
601{
602 std::optional<SimpleRange> range;
603 if (criteria.start == AccessibilitySearchTextStartFrom::Selection)
604 range = selectionRange();
605 else
606 range = elementRange();
607 if (!range)
608 return { };
609
610 if (criteria.start == AccessibilitySearchTextStartFrom::Begin)
611 range->end = range->start;
612 else if (criteria.start == AccessibilitySearchTextStartFrom::End)
613 range->start = range->end;
614 else if (criteria.direction == AccessibilitySearchTextDirection::Backward)
615 range->start = range->end;
616 else
617 range->end = range->start;
618
619 Vector<SimpleRange> result;
620 switch (criteria.direction) {
621 case AccessibilitySearchTextDirection::Forward:
622 case AccessibilitySearchTextDirection::Backward:
623 case AccessibilitySearchTextDirection::Closest:
624 if (auto foundRange = findTextRange(criteria.searchStrings, *range, criteria.direction))
625 result.append(*foundRange);
626 break;
627 case AccessibilitySearchTextDirection::All:
628 auto appendFoundRanges = [&](AccessibilitySearchTextDirection direction) {
629 for (auto foundRange = range; (foundRange = findTextRange(criteria.searchStrings, *foundRange, direction)); )
630 result.append(*foundRange);
631 };
632 appendFoundRanges(AccessibilitySearchTextDirection::Forward);
633 appendFoundRanges(AccessibilitySearchTextDirection::Backward);
634 break;
635 }
636 return result;
637}
638
639Vector<String> AccessibilityObject::performTextOperation(AccessibilityTextOperation const& operation)
640{
641 Vector<String> result;
642
643 if (operation.textRanges.isEmpty())
644 return result;
645
646 Frame* frame = this->frame();
647 if (!frame)
648 return result;
649
650 for (const auto& textRange : operation.textRanges) {
651 if (!frame->selection().setSelectedRange(textRange, Affinity::Downstream, FrameSelection::ShouldCloseTyping::Yes))
652 continue;
653
654 String text = plainText(textRange);
655 String replacementString = operation.replacementText;
656 bool replaceSelection = false;
657 switch (operation.type) {
658 case AccessibilityTextOperationType::Capitalize:
659 replacementString = capitalize(text, ' '); // FIXME: Needs to take locale into account to work correctly.
660 replaceSelection = true;
661 break;
662 case AccessibilityTextOperationType::Uppercase:
663 replacementString = text.convertToUppercaseWithoutLocale(); // FIXME: Needs locale to work correctly.
664 replaceSelection = true;
665 break;
666 case AccessibilityTextOperationType::Lowercase:
667 replacementString = text.convertToLowercaseWithoutLocale(); // FIXME: Needs locale to work correctly.
668 replaceSelection = true;
669 break;
670 case AccessibilityTextOperationType::Replace: {
671 replaceSelection = true;
672 // When applying find and replace activities, we want to match the capitalization of the replaced text,
673 // (unless we're replacing with an abbreviation.)
674 if (text.length() > 0
675 && replacementString.length() > 2
676 && replacementString != replacementString.convertToUppercaseWithoutLocale()) {
677 if (text[0] == u_toupper(text[0]))
678 replacementString = capitalize(replacementString, ' '); // FIXME: Needs to take locale into account to work correctly.
679 else
680 replacementString = replacementString.convertToLowercaseWithoutLocale(); // FIXME: Needs locale to work correctly.
681 }
682 break;
683 }
684 case AccessibilityTextOperationType::Select:
685 break;
686 }
687
688 // A bit obvious, but worth noting the API contract for this method is that we should
689 // return the replacement string when replacing, but the selected string if not.
690 if (replaceSelection) {
691 frame->editor().replaceSelectionWithText(replacementString, Editor::SelectReplacement::Yes, Editor::SmartReplace::Yes);
692 result.append(replacementString);
693 } else
694 result.append(text);
695 }
696
697 return result;
698}

700bool AccessibilityObject::hasAttributesRequiredForInclusion() const
701{
702 // These checks are simplified in the interest of execution speed.
703 if (!getAttribute(aria_helpAttr).isEmpty()
704 || !getAttribute(aria_describedbyAttr).isEmpty()
705 || !getAttribute(altAttr).isEmpty()
706 || !getAttribute(titleAttr).isEmpty())
707 return true;
708
709#if ENABLE(MATHML)
710 if (!getAttribute(MathMLNames::alttextAttr).isEmpty())
711 return true;
712#endif
713
714 return false;
715}

717bool AccessibilityObject::isARIAInput(AccessibilityRole ariaRole)
718{
719 switch (ariaRole) {
720 case AccessibilityRole::CheckBox:
721 case AccessibilityRole::RadioButton:
722 case AccessibilityRole::SearchField:
723 case AccessibilityRole::Switch:
724 case AccessibilityRole::TextField:
725 return true;
726 default:
727 return false;
728 }
729}
730
731bool AccessibilityObject::isARIAControl(AccessibilityRole ariaRole)
732{
733 if (isARIAInput(ariaRole))
734 return true;
735
736 switch (ariaRole) {
737 case AccessibilityRole::Button:
738 case AccessibilityRole::ComboBox:
739 case AccessibilityRole::ListBox:
740 case AccessibilityRole::PopUpButton:
741 case AccessibilityRole::Slider:
742 case AccessibilityRole::TextArea:
743 return true;
744 default:
745 return false;
746 }

779IntRect AccessibilityObject::boundingBoxForQuads(RenderObject* obj, const Vector<FloatQuad>& quads)
780{
781 ASSERT(obj);
782 if (!obj)
783 return IntRect();
784
785 FloatRect result;
786 for (const auto& quad : quads) {
787 FloatRect r = quad.enclosingBoundingBox();
788 if (!r.isEmpty()) {
789 if (obj->style().hasAppearance())
790 obj->theme().adjustRepaintRect(*obj, r);
791 result.unite(r);
792 }
793 }
794 return snappedIntRect(LayoutRect(result));

796
797bool AccessibilityObject::press()
798{
799 // The presence of the actionElement will confirm whether we should even attempt a press.
800 Element* actionElem = actionElement();
801 if (!actionElem)
802 return false;
803 if (Frame* f = actionElem->document().frame())
804 f->loader().resetMultipleFormSubmissionProtection();
805
806 // Hit test at this location to determine if there is a sub-node element that should act
807 // as the target of the action.
808 Element* hitTestElement = nullptr;
809 Document* document = this->document();
810 if (document) {
811 constexpr OptionSet<HitTestRequest::Type> hitType { HitTestRequest::Type::ReadOnly, HitTestRequest::Type::Active, HitTestRequest::Type::AccessibilityHitTest };
812 HitTestResult hitTestResult { clickPoint() };
813 document->hitTest(hitType, hitTestResult);
814 if (auto* innerNode = hitTestResult.innerNode()) {
815 if (auto* shadowHost = innerNode->shadowHost())
816 hitTestElement = shadowHost;
817 else if (is<Element>(*innerNode))
818 hitTestElement = &downcast<Element>(*innerNode);
819 else
820 hitTestElement = innerNode->parentElement();
821 }
822 }
823
824 // Prefer the actionElement instead of this node, if the actionElement is inside this node.
825 Element* pressElement = this->element();
826 if (!pressElement || actionElem->isDescendantOf(*pressElement))
827 pressElement = actionElem;
828
829 ASSERT(pressElement);
830 // Prefer the hit test element, if it is inside the target element.
831 if (hitTestElement && hitTestElement->isDescendantOf(*pressElement))
832 pressElement = hitTestElement;
833
834 UserGestureIndicator gestureIndicator(ProcessingUserGesture, document);
835
836 bool dispatchedEvent = false;
837#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
838 if (hasTouchEventListener())
839 dispatchedEvent = dispatchTouchEvent();
840#endif
841
842 return dispatchedEvent || pressElement->accessKeyAction(true) || pressElement->dispatchSimulatedClick(nullptr, SendMouseUpDownEvents);
843}
844
845bool AccessibilityObject::dispatchTouchEvent()
846{
847#if ENABLE(IOS_TOUCH_EVENTS)
848 if (auto* frame = mainFrame())
849 return frame->eventHandler().dispatchSimulatedTouchEvent(clickPoint());
850#endif
851 return false;
852}

880String AccessibilityObject::language() const
881{
882 const AtomString& lang = getAttribute(langAttr);
883 if (!lang.isEmpty())
884 return lang;
885
886 AccessibilityObject* parent = parentObject();
887
888 // as a last resort, fall back to the content language specified in the meta tag
889 if (!parent) {

891 if (doc)
892 return doc->contentLanguage();
893 return nullAtom();
894 }
895

899VisiblePositionRange AccessibilityObject::visiblePositionRangeForUnorderedPositions(const VisiblePosition& visiblePos1, const VisiblePosition& visiblePos2) const
900{
901 if (visiblePos1.isNull() || visiblePos2.isNull())
902 return VisiblePositionRange();
903
904 // If there's no common tree scope between positions, return early.
905 if (!commonTreeScope(visiblePos1.deepEquivalent().deprecatedNode(), visiblePos2.deepEquivalent().deprecatedNode()))
906 return VisiblePositionRange();
907
908 VisiblePosition startPos;
909 VisiblePosition endPos;
910 bool alreadyInOrder;
911
912 // upstream is ordered before downstream for the same position
913 if (visiblePos1 == visiblePos2 && visiblePos2.affinity() == Affinity::Upstream)
914 alreadyInOrder = false;
915
916 // use selection order to see if the positions are in order
917 else
918 alreadyInOrder = VisibleSelection(visiblePos1, visiblePos2).isBaseFirst();
919
920 if (alreadyInOrder) {
921 startPos = visiblePos1;
922 endPos = visiblePos2;
923 } else {
924 startPos = visiblePos2;
925 endPos = visiblePos1;
926 }
927
928 return { startPos, endPos };
929}

942
943static VisiblePosition updateAXLineStartForVisiblePosition(const VisiblePosition& visiblePosition)
944{
945 // A line in the accessibility sense should include floating objects, such as aligned image, as part of a line.
946 // So let's update the position to include that.
947 VisiblePosition tempPosition;
948 VisiblePosition startPosition = visiblePosition;
949 while (true) {
950 tempPosition = startPosition.previous();
951 if (tempPosition.isNull())
952 break;
953 Position p = tempPosition.deepEquivalent();
954 RenderObject* renderer = p.deprecatedNode()->renderer();
955 if (!renderer || (renderer->isRenderBlock() && !p.deprecatedEditingOffset()))
956 break;
957 if (!RenderedPosition(tempPosition).isNull())
958 break;
959 startPosition = tempPosition;
960 }
961
962 return startPosition;
963}
964
965VisiblePositionRange AccessibilityObject::leftLineVisiblePositionRange(const VisiblePosition& visiblePos) const
966{
967 if (visiblePos.isNull())
968 return VisiblePositionRange();
969
970 // make a caret selection for the position before marker position (to make sure
971 // we move off of a line start)
972 VisiblePosition prevVisiblePos = visiblePos.previous();
973 if (prevVisiblePos.isNull())
974 return VisiblePositionRange();
975
976 VisiblePosition startPosition = startOfLine(prevVisiblePos);
977
978 // keep searching for a valid line start position. Unless the VisiblePosition is at the very beginning, there should
979 // always be a valid line range. However, startOfLine will return null for position next to a floating object,
980 // since floating object doesn't really belong to any line.
981 // This check will reposition the marker before the floating object, to ensure we get a line start.
982 if (startPosition.isNull()) {
983 while (startPosition.isNull() && prevVisiblePos.isNotNull()) {
984 prevVisiblePos = prevVisiblePos.previous();
985 startPosition = startOfLine(prevVisiblePos);
986 }
987 } else
988 startPosition = updateAXLineStartForVisiblePosition(startPosition);
989
990 return { startPosition, endOfLine(prevVisiblePos) };
991}
992
993VisiblePositionRange AccessibilityObject::rightLineVisiblePositionRange(const VisiblePosition& visiblePos) const
994{
995 if (visiblePos.isNull())
996 return VisiblePositionRange();
997
998 // make sure we move off of a line end
999 VisiblePosition nextVisiblePos = visiblePos.next();
1000 if (nextVisiblePos.isNull())
1001 return VisiblePositionRange();
1002
1003 VisiblePosition startPosition = startOfLine(nextVisiblePos);
1004
1005 // fetch for a valid line start position
1006 if (startPosition.isNull()) {
1007 startPosition = visiblePos;
1008 nextVisiblePos = nextVisiblePos.next();
1009 } else
1010 startPosition = updateAXLineStartForVisiblePosition(startPosition);
1011
1012 VisiblePosition endPosition = endOfLine(nextVisiblePos);
1013
1014 // as long as the position hasn't reached the end of the doc, keep searching for a valid line end position
1015 // Unless the VisiblePosition is at the very end, there should always be a valid line range. However, endOfLine will
1016 // return null for position by a floating object, since floating object doesn't really belong to any line.
1017 // This check will reposition the marker after the floating object, to ensure we get a line end.
1018 while (endPosition.isNull() && nextVisiblePos.isNotNull()) {
1019 nextVisiblePos = nextVisiblePos.next();
1020 endPosition = endOfLine(nextVisiblePos);
1021 }
1022
1023 return { startPosition, endPosition };
1024}

1040static VisiblePosition startOfStyleRange(const VisiblePosition& visiblePos)
1041{
1042 RenderObject* renderer = visiblePos.deepEquivalent().deprecatedNode()->renderer();
1043 RenderObject* startRenderer = renderer;
1044 auto* style = &renderer->style();
1045
1046 // traverse backward by renderer to look for style change
1047 for (RenderObject* r = renderer->previousInPreOrder(); r; r = r->previousInPreOrder()) {
1048 // skip non-leaf nodes
1049 if (r->firstChildSlow())
1050 continue;
1051
1052 // stop at style change
1053 if (&r->style() != style)
1054 break;
1055
1056 // remember match
1057 startRenderer = r;
1058 }
1059
1060 return firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(startRenderer->node());
1061}
1062
1063static VisiblePosition endOfStyleRange(const VisiblePosition& visiblePos)
1064{
1065 RenderObject* renderer = visiblePos.deepEquivalent().deprecatedNode()->renderer();
1066 RenderObject* endRenderer = renderer;
1067 const RenderStyle& style = renderer->style();
1068
1069 // traverse forward by renderer to look for style change
1070 for (RenderObject* r = renderer->nextInPreOrder(); r; r = r->nextInPreOrder()) {
1071 // skip non-leaf nodes
1072 if (r->firstChildSlow())
1073 continue;
1074
1075 // stop at style change
1076 if (&r->style() != &style)
1077 break;
1078
1079 // remember match
1080 endRenderer = r;
1081 }
1082
1083 return lastPositionInOrAfterNode(endRenderer->node());
1084}

1106std::optional<SimpleRange> AccessibilityObject::rangeForPlainTextRange(const PlainTextRange& range) const
1107{
1108 unsigned textLength = getLengthForTextRange();
1109 if (range.start + range.length > textLength)
1110 return std::nullopt;
1111 // Avoid setting selection to uneditable parent node in FrameSelection::setSelectedRange. See webkit.org/b/206093.
1112 if (range.isNull() && !textLength)
1113 return std::nullopt;
1114
1115 if (AXObjectCache* cache = axObjectCache()) {
1116 CharacterOffset start = cache->characterOffsetForIndex(range.start, this);
1117 CharacterOffset end = cache->characterOffsetForIndex(range.start + range.length, this);
1118 return cache->rangeForUnorderedCharacterOffsets(start, end);
1119 }
1120 return std::nullopt;

1128bool AccessibilityObject::replacedNodeNeedsCharacter(Node* replacedNode)
1129{
1130 // we should always be given a rendered node and a replaced node, but be safe
1131 // replaced nodes are either attachments (widgets) or images
1132 if (!replacedNode || !isRendererReplacedElement(replacedNode->renderer()) || replacedNode->isTextNode())
1133 return false;
1134
1135 // create an AX object, but skip it if it is not supposed to be seen
1136 AccessibilityObject* object = replacedNode->renderer()->document().axObjectCache()->getOrCreate(replacedNode);
1137 if (object->accessibilityIsIgnored())
1138 return false;
1139
1140 return true;
1141}

1143// Finds a RenderListItem parent give a node.
1144static RenderListItem* renderListItemContainerForNode(Node* node)
1145{
1146 for (; node; node = node->parentNode()) {
1147 RenderBoxModelObject* renderer = node->renderBoxModelObject();
1148 if (is<RenderListItem>(renderer))
1149 return downcast<RenderListItem>(renderer);
1150 }
1151 return nullptr;
1152}
1153
1154static String listMarkerTextForNode(Node* node)
1155{
1156 RenderListItem* listItem = renderListItemContainerForNode(node);
1157 if (!listItem)
1158 return String();
1159
1160 // If this is in a list item, we need to manually add the text for the list marker
1161 // because a RenderListMarker does not have a Node equivalent and thus does not appear
1162 // when iterating text.
1163 return listItem->markerTextWithSuffix().toString();
1164}
1165
1166// Returns the text associated with a list marker if this node is contained within a list item.
1167String AccessibilityObject::listMarkerTextForNodeAndPosition(Node* node, const VisiblePosition& visiblePositionStart)
1168{
1169 // If the range does not contain the start of the line, the list marker text should not be included.
1170 if (!isStartOfLine(visiblePositionStart))
1171 return String();
1172
1173 // We should speak the list marker only for the first line.
1174 RenderListItem* listItem = renderListItemContainerForNode(node);
1175 if (!listItem)
1176 return String();
1177 if (!inSameLine(visiblePositionStart, firstPositionInNode(&listItem->element())))
1178 return String();
1179
1180 return listMarkerTextForNode(node);
1181}
1182
1183String AccessibilityObject::stringForRange(const SimpleRange& range) const
1184{
1185 TextIterator it(range);
1186 if (it.atEnd())
1187 return String();
1188
1189 StringBuilder builder;
1190 for (; !it.atEnd(); it.advance()) {
1191 // non-zero length means textual node, zero length means replaced node (AKA "attachments" in AX)
1192 if (it.text().length()) {
1193 // Add a textual representation for list marker text.
1194 // Don't add list marker text for new line character.
1195 if (it.text().length() != 1 || !isSpaceOrNewline(it.text()[0])) {
1196 // FIXME: Seems like the position should be based on it.range(), not range.
1197 builder.append(listMarkerTextForNodeAndPosition(it.node(), VisiblePosition(makeDeprecatedLegacyPosition(range.start))));
1198 }
1199 it.appendTextToStringBuilder(builder);
1200 } else {
1201 if (replacedNodeNeedsCharacter(it.node()))
1202 builder.append(objectReplacementCharacter);
1203 }
1204 }
1205
1206 return builder.toString();
1207}
1208
1209String AccessibilityObject::stringForVisiblePositionRange(const VisiblePositionRange& visiblePositionRange)
1210{
1211 auto range = makeSimpleRange(visiblePositionRange);
1212 if (!range)
1213 return { };
1214
1215 StringBuilder builder;
1216 for (TextIterator it(*range); !it.atEnd(); it.advance()) {
1217 // non-zero length means textual node, zero length means replaced node (AKA "attachments" in AX)
1218 if (it.text().length()) {
1219 // Add a textual representation for list marker text.
1220 builder.append(listMarkerTextForNodeAndPosition(it.node(), visiblePositionRange.start));
1221 it.appendTextToStringBuilder(builder);
1222 } else {
1223 // locate the node and starting offset for this replaced range
1224 if (replacedNodeNeedsCharacter(it.node()))
1225 builder.append(objectReplacementCharacter);
1226 }
1227 }
1228 return builder.toString();
1229}
1230
1231int AccessibilityObject::lengthForVisiblePositionRange(const VisiblePositionRange& visiblePositionRange) const
1232{
1233 // FIXME: Multi-byte support
1234
1235 auto range = makeSimpleRange(visiblePositionRange);
1236 if (!range)
1237 return -1; // FIXME: Why not return 0?
1238
1239 // FIXME: Use characterCount instead of writing our own loop?
1240 int length = 0;
1241 for (TextIterator it(*range); !it.atEnd(); it.advance()) {
1242 // non-zero length means textual node, zero length means replaced node (AKA "attachments" in AX)
1243 if (it.text().length())
1244 length += it.text().length();
1245 else {
1246 if (replacedNodeNeedsCharacter(it.node()))
1247 ++length;
1248 }
1249 }
1250 return length;
1251}

1253VisiblePosition AccessibilityObject::visiblePositionForBounds(const IntRect& rect, AccessibilityVisiblePositionForBounds visiblePositionForBounds) const
1254{
1255 if (rect.isEmpty())
1256 return VisiblePosition();
1257
1258 auto* mainFrame = this->mainFrame();
1259 if (!mainFrame)
1260 return VisiblePosition();
1261
1262 // FIXME: Add support for right-to-left languages.
1263 IntPoint corner = (visiblePositionForBounds == AccessibilityVisiblePositionForBounds::First) ? rect.minXMinYCorner() : rect.maxXMaxYCorner();
1264 VisiblePosition position = mainFrame->visiblePositionForPoint(corner);
1265
1266 if (rect.contains(position.absoluteCaretBounds().center()))
1267 return position;
1268
1269 // If the initial position is located outside the bounds adjust it incrementally as needed.
1270 VisiblePosition nextPosition = position.next();
1271 VisiblePosition previousPosition = position.previous();
1272 while (nextPosition.isNotNull() || previousPosition.isNotNull()) {
1273 if (rect.contains(nextPosition.absoluteCaretBounds().center()))
1274 return nextPosition;
1275 if (rect.contains(previousPosition.absoluteCaretBounds().center()))
1276 return previousPosition;
1277
1278 nextPosition = nextPosition.next();
1279 previousPosition = previousPosition.previous();
1280 }
1281
1282 return VisiblePosition();
1283}

1451 auto role = roleValue();

1453 || role == AccessibilityRole::MenuItemCheckbox
1454 || role == AccessibilityRole::MenuItemRadio
1455 || role == AccessibilityRole::Switch
1456 || isToggleButton();
1457}

1460{
1461 return (isComboBox() || isARIATextControl()) && hasAttribute(aria_autocompleteAttr);
1462}

1464String AccessibilityObject::autoCompleteValue() const
1465{
1466 const AtomString& autoComplete = getAttribute(aria_autocompleteAttr);
1467 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(autoComplete, "inline")
1468 || equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(autoComplete, "list")
1469 || equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(autoComplete, "both"))
1470 return autoComplete;
1471
1472 return "none";

1475bool AccessibilityObject::contentEditableAttributeIsEnabled(Element* element)
1476{
1477 if (!element)
1478 return false;
1479
1480 const AtomString& contentEditableValue = element->attributeWithoutSynchronization(contenteditableAttr);
1481 if (contentEditableValue.isNull())
1482 return false;
1483
1484 // Both "true" (case-insensitive) and the empty string count as true.
1485 return contentEditableValue.isEmpty() || equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(contentEditableValue, "true");
1486}

1488#if ENABLE(ACCESSIBILITY)
1489int AccessibilityObject::lineForPosition(const VisiblePosition& visiblePos) const
1490{
1491 if (visiblePos.isNull() || !node())
1492 return -1;
1493
1494 // If the position is not in the same editable region as this AX object, return -1.
1495 Node* containerNode = visiblePos.deepEquivalent().containerNode();
1496 if (!containerNode->containsIncludingShadowDOM(node()) && !node()->containsIncludingShadowDOM(containerNode))
1497 return -1;
1498
1499 int lineCount = -1;
1500 VisiblePosition currentVisiblePos = visiblePos;
1501 VisiblePosition savedVisiblePos;
1502
1503 // move up until we get to the top
1504 // FIXME: This only takes us to the top of the rootEditableElement, not the top of the
1505 // top document.
1506 do {
1507 savedVisiblePos = currentVisiblePos;
1508 VisiblePosition prevVisiblePos = previousLinePosition(currentVisiblePos, 0, HasEditableAXRole);
1509 currentVisiblePos = prevVisiblePos;
1510 ++lineCount;
1511 } while (currentVisiblePos.isNotNull() && !(inSameLine(currentVisiblePos, savedVisiblePos)));
1512
1513 return lineCount;
1514}
1515#endif

1517// NOTE: Consider providing this utility method as AX API
1518PlainTextRange AccessibilityObject::plainTextRangeForVisiblePositionRange(const VisiblePositionRange& positionRange) const
1519{
1520 int index1 = index(positionRange.start);
1521 int index2 = index(positionRange.end);
1522 if (index1 < 0 || index2 < 0 || index1 > index2)
1523 return PlainTextRange();
1524
1525 return PlainTextRange(index1, index2 - index1);
1526}
1527
1528// The composed character range in the text associated with this accessibility object that
1529// is specified by the given screen coordinates. This parameterized attribute returns the
1530// complete range of characters (including surrogate pairs of multi-byte glyphs) at the given
1531// screen coordinates.
1532// NOTE: This varies from AppKit when the point is below the last line. AppKit returns an
1533// an error in that case. We return textControl->text().length(), 1. Does this matter?
1534PlainTextRange AccessibilityObject::doAXRangeForPosition(const IntPoint& point) const
1535{
1536 int i = index(visiblePositionForPoint(point));
1537 if (i < 0)
1538 return PlainTextRange();
1539
1540 return PlainTextRange(i, 1);
1541}
1542
1543// Given a character index, the range of text associated with this accessibility object
1544// over which the style in effect at that character index applies.
1545PlainTextRange AccessibilityObject::doAXStyleRangeForIndex(unsigned index) const
1546{
1547 VisiblePositionRange range = styleRangeForPosition(visiblePositionForIndex(index, false));
1548 return plainTextRangeForVisiblePositionRange(range);
1549}
1550
1551// Given an indexed character, the line number of the text associated with this accessibility
1552// object that contains the character.
1553unsigned AccessibilityObject::doAXLineForIndex(unsigned index)
1554{
1555 return lineForPosition(visiblePositionForIndex(index, false));
1556}

1695
1696void AccessibilityObject::ariaTreeRows(AccessibilityChildrenVector& result)
1697{
1698 // If the element specifies its tree rows through aria-owns, return that first.
1699 AccessibilityChildrenVector ariaOwns;
1700 ariaOwnsElements(ariaOwns);
1701 if (ariaOwns.size()) {
1702 result.appendVector(ariaOwns);
1703 return;
1704 }
1705
1706 for (const auto& child : children()) {
1707 // Add tree items as the rows.
1708 if (child->roleValue() == AccessibilityRole::TreeItem)
1709 result.append(child);
1710
1711 // Now see if this item also has rows hiding inside of it.
1712 child->ariaTreeRows(result);
1713 }
1714}
1715
1716void AccessibilityObject::ariaTreeItemContent(AccessibilityChildrenVector& result)
1717{
1718 // The ARIA tree item content are the item that are not other tree items or their containing groups.
1719 for (const auto& child : children()) {
1720 if (!child->isGroup() && child->roleValue() != AccessibilityRole::TreeItem)
1721 result.append(child);
1722 }
1723}
1724
1725AXCoreObject::AccessibilityChildrenVector AccessibilityObject::disclosedRows()
1726{
1727 AccessibilityChildrenVector result;
1728
1729 for (const auto& obj : children()) {
1730 // Add tree items as the rows.
1731 if (obj->roleValue() == AccessibilityRole::TreeItem)
1732 result.append(obj);
1733 // If it's not a tree item, then descend into the group to find more tree items.
1734 else
1735 obj->ariaTreeRows(result);
1736 }
1737
1738 return result;
1739}

1807
1808String AccessibilityObject::invalidStatus() const
1809{
1810 String grammarValue = "grammar"_s;
1811 String falseValue = "false"_s;
1812 String spellingValue = "spelling"_s;
1813 String trueValue = "true"_s;
1814 String undefinedValue = "undefined"_s;
1815
1816 // aria-invalid can return false (default), grammar, spelling, or true.
1817 String ariaInvalid = stripLeadingAndTrailingHTMLSpaces(getAttribute(aria_invalidAttr));
1818
1819 if (ariaInvalid.isEmpty()) {
1820 // We should expose invalid status for input types.
1821 Node* node = this->node();
1822 if (node && is<HTMLInputElement>(*node)) {
1823 HTMLInputElement& input = downcast<HTMLInputElement>(*node);
1824 if (input.hasBadInput() || input.typeMismatch())
1825 return trueValue;
1826 }
1827 return falseValue;
1828 }
1829
1830 // If "false", "undefined" [sic, string value], empty, or missing, return "false".
1831 if (ariaInvalid == falseValue || ariaInvalid == undefinedValue)
1832 return falseValue;
1833 // Besides true/false/undefined, the only tokens defined by WAI-ARIA 1.0...
1834 // ...for @aria-invalid are "grammar" and "spelling".
1835 if (ariaInvalid == grammarValue)
1836 return grammarValue;
1837 if (ariaInvalid == spellingValue)
1838 return spellingValue;
1839 // Any other non empty string should be treated as "true".
1840 return trueValue;
1841}

1843bool AccessibilityObject::supportsCurrent() const
1844{
1845 return hasAttribute(aria_currentAttr);
1846}
1847
1848AccessibilityCurrentState AccessibilityObject::currentState() const
1849{
1850 // aria-current can return false (default), true, page, step, location, date or time.
1851 String currentStateValue = stripLeadingAndTrailingHTMLSpaces(getAttribute(aria_currentAttr));
1852
1853 // If "false", empty, or missing, return false state.
1854 if (currentStateValue.isEmpty() || currentStateValue == "false")
1855 return AccessibilityCurrentState::False;
1856
1857 if (currentStateValue == "page")
1858 return AccessibilityCurrentState::Page;
1859 if (currentStateValue == "step")
1860 return AccessibilityCurrentState::Step;
1861 if (currentStateValue == "location")
1862 return AccessibilityCurrentState::Location;
1863 if (currentStateValue == "date")
1864 return AccessibilityCurrentState::Date;
1865 if (currentStateValue == "time")
1866 return AccessibilityCurrentState::Time;
1867
1868 // Any value not included in the list of allowed values should be treated as "true".
1869 return AccessibilityCurrentState::True;
1870}
1871
1872String AccessibilityObject::currentValue() const
1873{
1874 switch (currentState()) {
1875 case AccessibilityCurrentState::False:
1876 return "false";
1877 case AccessibilityCurrentState::Page:
1878 return "page";
1879 case AccessibilityCurrentState::Step:
1880 return "step";
1881 case AccessibilityCurrentState::Location:
1882 return "location";
1883 case AccessibilityCurrentState::Time:
1884 return "time";
1885 case AccessibilityCurrentState::Date:
1886 return "date";
1887 default:
1888 case AccessibilityCurrentState::True:
1889 return "true";
1890 }
1891}

1893bool AccessibilityObject::isModalDescendant(Node* modalNode) const
1894{
1895 Node* node = this->node();
1896 if (!modalNode || !node)
1897 return false;
1898
1899 if (node == modalNode)
1900 return true;
1901
1902 // ARIA 1.1 aria-modal, indicates whether an element is modal when displayed.
1903 // For the decendants of the modal object, they should also be considered as aria-modal=true.
1904 return node->isDescendantOf(*modalNode);
1905}

1908{

1910 return node() && cache->modalNode() == node();
1911
1912 return false;
1913}
1914
1915bool AccessibilityObject::ignoredFromModalPresence() const
1916{
1917 // We shouldn't ignore the top node.
1918 if (!node() || !node()->parentNode())
1919 return false;
1920
1921 AXObjectCache* cache = axObjectCache();
1922 if (!cache)
1923 return false;
1924
1925 // modalNode is the current displayed modal dialog.
1926 Node* modalNode = cache->modalNode();
1927 if (!modalNode)
1928 return false;
1929
1930 // We only want to ignore the objects within the same frame as the modal dialog.
1931 if (modalNode->document().frame() != this->frame())
1932 return false;
1933
1934 return !isModalDescendant(modalNode);
1935}

1964bool AccessibilityObject::replaceTextInRange(const String& replacementString, const PlainTextRange& range)
1965{
1966 // If this is being called on the web area, redirect it to be on the body, which will have a renderer associated with it.
1967 if (is<Document>(node())) {
1968 if (auto bodyObject = axObjectCache()->getOrCreate(downcast<Document>(node())->body()))
1969 return bodyObject->replaceTextInRange(replacementString, range);
1970 return false;
1971 }
1972
1973 if (!renderer() || !is<Element>(node()))
1974 return false;
1975
1976 auto& element = downcast<Element>(*renderer()->node());
1977
1978 // We should use the editor's insertText to mimic typing into the field.
1979 // Also only do this when the field is in editing mode.
1980 auto& frame = renderer()->frame();
1981 if (element.shouldUseInputMethod()) {
1982 frame.selection().setSelectedRange(rangeForPlainTextRange(range), Affinity::Downstream, FrameSelection::ShouldCloseTyping::Yes);
1983 frame.editor().replaceSelectionWithText(replacementString, Editor::SelectReplacement::No, Editor::SmartReplace::No);
1984 return true;
1985 }
1986
1987 if (is<HTMLInputElement>(element)) {
1988 downcast<HTMLInputElement>(element).setRangeText(replacementString, range.start, range.length, "");
1989 return true;
1990 }
1991 if (is<HTMLTextAreaElement>(element)) {
1992 downcast<HTMLTextAreaElement>(element).setRangeText(replacementString, range.start, range.length, "");
1993 return true;
1994 }
1995
1996 return false;
1997}
1998
1999bool AccessibilityObject::insertText(const String& text)
2000{
2001 if (!renderer() || !is<Element>(node()))
2002 return false;
2003
2004 auto& element = downcast<Element>(*renderer()->node());
2005
2006 // Only try to insert text if the field is in editing mode.
2007 if (!element.shouldUseInputMethod())
2008 return false;
2009
2010 // Use Editor::insertText to mimic typing into the field.
2011 auto& editor = renderer()->frame().editor();
2012 return editor.insertText(text, nullptr);
2013}

2015// Lacking concrete evidence of orientation, horizontal means width > height. vertical is height > width;
2016AccessibilityOrientation AccessibilityObject::orientation() const
2017{
2018 LayoutRect bounds = elementRect();
2019 if (bounds.size().width() > bounds.size().height())
2020 return AccessibilityOrientation::Horizontal;
2021 if (bounds.size().height() > bounds.size().width())
2022 return AccessibilityOrientation::Vertical;
2023
2024 return AccessibilityOrientation::Undefined;
2025}

2201AccessibilityRole AccessibilityObject::ariaRoleToWebCoreRole(const String& value)
2202{
2203 if (value.isNull() || value.isEmpty())
2204 return AccessibilityRole::Unknown;
2205
2206 for (auto roleName : StringView(value).split(' ')) {
2207 AccessibilityRole role = ariaRoleMap().get<ASCIICaseInsensitiveStringViewHashTranslator>(roleName);
2208 if (static_cast<int>(role))
2209 return role;
2210 }
2211 return AccessibilityRole::Unknown;

2214String AccessibilityObject::computedRoleString() const
2215{
2216 // FIXME: Need a few special cases that aren't in the RoleMap: option, etc. http://webkit.org/b/128296
2217 AccessibilityRole role = roleValue();
2218
2219 if (role == AccessibilityRole::Image && accessibilityIsIgnored())
2220 return reverseAriaRoleMap().get(static_cast<int>(AccessibilityRole::Presentational));
2221
2222 // We do not compute a role string for generic block elements with user-agent assigned roles.
2223 if (role == AccessibilityRole::Group || role == AccessibilityRole::TextGroup)
2224 return "";
2225
2226 // We do compute a role string for block elements with author-provided roles.
2227 if (role == AccessibilityRole::ApplicationTextGroup
2228 || role == AccessibilityRole::Footnote
2229 || role == AccessibilityRole::GraphicsObject)
2230 return reverseAriaRoleMap().get(static_cast<int>(AccessibilityRole::ApplicationGroup));
2231
2232 if (role == AccessibilityRole::GraphicsDocument)
2233 return reverseAriaRoleMap().get(static_cast<int>(AccessibilityRole::Document));
2234
2235 if (role == AccessibilityRole::GraphicsSymbol)
2236 return reverseAriaRoleMap().get(static_cast<int>(AccessibilityRole::Image));
2237
2238 if (role == AccessibilityRole::HorizontalRule)
2239 return reverseAriaRoleMap().get(static_cast<int>(AccessibilityRole::Splitter));
2240
2241 if (role == AccessibilityRole::PopUpButton || role == AccessibilityRole::ToggleButton)
2242 return reverseAriaRoleMap().get(static_cast<int>(AccessibilityRole::Button));
2243
2244 if (role == AccessibilityRole::LandmarkDocRegion)
2245 return reverseAriaRoleMap().get(static_cast<int>(AccessibilityRole::LandmarkRegion));
2246
2247 return reverseAriaRoleMap().get(static_cast<int>(role));
2248}

2354bool AccessibilityObject::supportsPressAction() const
2355{
2356 if (isButton())
2357 return true;
2358 if (roleValue() == AccessibilityRole::Details)
2359 return true;
2360
2361 Element* actionElement = this->actionElement();
2362 if (!actionElement)
2363 return false;
2364
2365 // [Bug: 136247] Heuristic: element handlers that have more than one accessible descendant should not be exposed as supporting press.
2366 if (actionElement != element()) {
2367 if (AccessibilityObject* axObj = axObjectCache()->getOrCreate(actionElement)) {
2368 AccessibilityChildrenVector results;
2369 // Search within for immediate descendants that are static text. If we find more than one
2370 // then this is an event delegator actionElement and we should expose the press action.
2371 Vector<AccessibilitySearchKey> keys({ AccessibilitySearchKey::StaticText, AccessibilitySearchKey::Control, AccessibilitySearchKey::Graphic, AccessibilitySearchKey::Heading, AccessibilitySearchKey::Link });
2372 AccessibilitySearchCriteria criteria(axObj, AccessibilitySearchDirection::Next, emptyString(), 2, false, false);
2373 criteria.searchKeys = keys;
2374 axObj->findMatchingObjects(&criteria, results);
2375 if (results.size() > 1)
2376 return false;
2377 }
2378 }
2379
2380 // [Bug: 133613] Heuristic: If the action element is presentational, we shouldn't expose press as a supported action.
2381 return !nodeHasPresentationRole(actionElement);
2382}

2508AXCoreObject* AccessibilityObject::elementAccessibilityHitTest(const IntPoint& point) const
2509{
2510 // Send the hit test back into the sub-frame if necessary.
2511 if (isAttachment()) {
2512 Widget* widget = widgetForAttachmentView();
2513 // Normalize the point for the widget's bounds.
2514 if (widget && widget->isFrameView()) {
2515 if (AXObjectCache* cache = axObjectCache())
2516 return cache->getOrCreate(widget)->accessibilityHitTest(IntPoint(point - widget->frameRect().location()));
2517 }
2518 }
2519
2520 // Check if there are any mock elements that need to be handled.
2521 for (const auto& child : m_children) {
2522 if (child->isMockObject() && child->elementRect().contains(point))
2523 return child->elementAccessibilityHitTest(point);
2524 }
2525
2526 return const_cast<AccessibilityObject*>(this);
2527}

2541
2542void AccessibilityObject::setFocused(bool focus)
2543{
2544 if (focus) {
2545 // Ensure that the view is focused and active, otherwise, any attempt to set focus to an object inside it will fail.
2546 auto* document = this->document();
2547 if (!document)
2548 return;
2549
2550 auto* frame = document->frame();
2551 if (frame && frame->selection().isFocusedAndActive())
2552 return; // Nothing to do, already focused and active.
2553
2554 auto* page = document->page();
2555 if (!page)
2556 return;
2557
2558 ChromeClient& chromeClient = page->chrome().client();
2559 chromeClient.focus();
2560
2561#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
2562 auto* frameView = documentFrameView();
2563 if (!frameView)
2564 return;
2565
2566 // Legacy WebKit1 case.
2567 if (frameView->platformWidget())
2568 chromeClient.makeFirstResponder((NSResponder *)frameView->platformWidget());
2569 else
2570 chromeClient.assistiveTechnologyMakeFirstResponder();
2571#endif
2572 }
2573}

2575AccessibilitySortDirection AccessibilityObject::sortDirection() const
2576{
2577 // Only objects that are descendant of column or row headers are allowed to have sort direction.
2578 auto* header = Accessibility::findAncestor<AccessibilityObject>(*this, true, [] (const AccessibilityObject& object) {
2579 auto role = object.roleValue();
2580 return role == AccessibilityRole::ColumnHeader || role == AccessibilityRole::RowHeader;
2581 });
2582 if (!header)
2583 return AccessibilitySortDirection::Invalid;
2584
2585 auto& sortAttribute = header->getAttribute(aria_sortAttr);
2586 if (sortAttribute.isNull())
2587 return AccessibilitySortDirection::None;
2588
2589 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(sortAttribute, "ascending"))
2590 return AccessibilitySortDirection::Ascending;
2591 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(sortAttribute, "descending"))
2592 return AccessibilitySortDirection::Descending;
2593 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(sortAttribute, "other"))
2594 return AccessibilitySortDirection::Other;
2595
2596 return AccessibilitySortDirection::None;
2597}

2613
2614String AccessibilityObject::popupValue() const
2615{
2616 static const NeverDestroyed<MemoryCompactLookupOnlyRobinHoodHashSet<String>> allowedPopupValues(std::initializer_list<String> {
2617 "menu"_s, "listbox"_s, "tree"_s, "grid"_s, "dialog"_s,
2618 });
2619
2620 auto hasPopup = getAttribute(aria_haspopupAttr).convertToASCIILowercase();
2621 if (hasPopup.isNull() || hasPopup.isEmpty()) {
2622 // In ARIA 1.1, the implicit value for combobox became "listbox."
2623 if (isComboBox() || hasDatalist())
2624 return "listbox";
2625 return "false";
2626 }
2627
2628 if (allowedPopupValues->contains(hasPopup))
2629 return hasPopup;
2630
2631 // aria-haspopup specification states that true must be treated as menu.
2632 if (hasPopup == "true")
2633 return "menu";
2634
2635 // The spec states that "User agents must treat any value of aria-haspopup that is not
2636 // included in the list of allowed values, including an empty string, as if the value
2637 // false had been provided."
2638 return "false";
2639}

2765
2766AccessibilityButtonState AccessibilityObject::checkboxOrRadioValue() const
2767{
2768 // If this is a real checkbox or radio button, AccessibilityRenderObject will handle.
2769 // If it's an ARIA checkbox, radio, or switch the aria-checked attribute should be used.
2770 // If it's a toggle button, the aria-pressed attribute is consulted.
2771
2772 if (isToggleButton()) {
2773 const AtomString& ariaPressed = getAttribute(aria_pressedAttr);
2774 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(ariaPressed, "true"))
2775 return AccessibilityButtonState::On;
2776 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(ariaPressed, "mixed"))
2777 return AccessibilityButtonState::Mixed;
2778 return AccessibilityButtonState::Off;
2779 }
2780
2781 const AtomString& result = getAttribute(aria_checkedAttr);
2782 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(result, "true"))
2783 return AccessibilityButtonState::On;
2784 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(result, "mixed")) {
2785 // ARIA says that radio, menuitemradio, and switch elements must NOT expose button state mixed.
2786 AccessibilityRole ariaRole = ariaRoleAttribute();
2787 if (ariaRole == AccessibilityRole::RadioButton || ariaRole == AccessibilityRole::MenuItemRadio || ariaRole == AccessibilityRole::Switch)
2788 return AccessibilityButtonState::Off;
2789 return AccessibilityButtonState::Mixed;
2790 }
2791
2792 if (isIndeterminate())
2793 return AccessibilityButtonState::Mixed;
2794
2795 return AccessibilityButtonState::Off;
2796}

2815
2816// This is a 1-dimensional scroll offset helper function that's applied
2817// separately in the horizontal and vertical directions, because the
2818// logic is the same. The goal is to compute the best scroll offset
2819// in order to make an object visible within a viewport.
2820//
2821// If the object is already fully visible, returns the same scroll
2822// offset.
2823//
2824// In case the whole object cannot fit, you can specify a
2825// subfocus - a smaller region within the object that should
2826// be prioritized. If the whole object can fit, the subfocus is
2827// ignored.
2828//
2829// If possible, the object and subfocus are centered within the
2830// viewport.
2831//
2832// Example 1: the object is already visible, so nothing happens.
2833// +----------Viewport---------+
2834// +---Object---+
2835// +--SubFocus--+
2836//
2837// Example 2: the object is not fully visible, so it's centered
2838// within the viewport.
2839// Before:
2840// +----------Viewport---------+
2841// +---Object---+
2842// +--SubFocus--+
2843//
2844// After:
2845// +----------Viewport---------+
2846// +---Object---+
2847// +--SubFocus--+
2848//
2849// Example 3: the object is larger than the viewport, so the
2850// viewport moves to show as much of the object as possible,
2851// while also trying to center the subfocus.
2852// Before:
2853// +----------Viewport---------+
2854// +---------------Object--------------+
2855// +-SubFocus-+
2856//
2857// After:
2858// +----------Viewport---------+
2859// +---------------Object--------------+
2860// +-SubFocus-+
2861//
2862// When constraints cannot be fully satisfied, the min
2863// (left/top) position takes precedence over the max (right/bottom).
2864//
2865// Note that the return value represents the ideal new scroll offset.
2866// This may be out of range - the calling function should clip this
2867// to the available range.
2868static int computeBestScrollOffset(int currentScrollOffset, int subfocusMin, int subfocusMax, int objectMin, int objectMax, int viewportMin, int viewportMax)
2869{
2870 int viewportSize = viewportMax - viewportMin;
2871
2872 // If the object size is larger than the viewport size, consider
2873 // only a portion that's as large as the viewport, centering on
2874 // the subfocus as much as possible.
2875 if (objectMax - objectMin > viewportSize) {
2876 // Since it's impossible to fit the whole object in the
2877 // viewport, exit now if the subfocus is already within the viewport.
2878 if (subfocusMin - currentScrollOffset >= viewportMin && subfocusMax - currentScrollOffset <= viewportMax)
2879 return currentScrollOffset;
2880
2881 // Subfocus must be within focus.
2882 subfocusMin = std::max(subfocusMin, objectMin);
2883 subfocusMax = std::min(subfocusMax, objectMax);
2884
2885 // Subfocus must be no larger than the viewport size; favor top/left.
2886 if (subfocusMax - subfocusMin > viewportSize)
2887 subfocusMax = subfocusMin + viewportSize;
2888
2889 // Compute the size of an object centered on the subfocus, the size of the viewport.
2890 int centeredObjectMin = (subfocusMin + subfocusMax - viewportSize) / 2;
2891 int centeredObjectMax = centeredObjectMin + viewportSize;
2892
2893 objectMin = std::max(objectMin, centeredObjectMin);
2894 objectMax = std::min(objectMax, centeredObjectMax);
2895 }
2896
2897 // Exit now if the focus is already within the viewport.
2898 if (objectMin - currentScrollOffset >= viewportMin
2899 && objectMax - currentScrollOffset <= viewportMax)
2900 return currentScrollOffset;
2901
2902 // Center the object in the viewport.
2903 return (objectMin + objectMax - viewportMin - viewportMax) / 2;
2904}
2905
2906bool AccessibilityObject::isOnScreen() const
2907{
2908 bool isOnscreen = true;
2909
2910 // To figure out if the element is onscreen, we start by building of a stack starting with the
2911 // element, and then include every scrollable parent in the hierarchy.
2912 Vector<const AccessibilityObject*> objects;
2913
2914 objects.append(this);
2915 for (AccessibilityObject* parentObject = this->parentObject(); parentObject; parentObject = parentObject->parentObject()) {
2916 if (parentObject->getScrollableAreaIfScrollable())
2917 objects.append(parentObject);
2918 }
2919
2920 // Now, go back through that chain and make sure each inner object is within the
2921 // visible bounds of the outer object.
2922 size_t levels = objects.size() - 1;
2923
2924 for (size_t i = levels; i >= 1; i--) {
2925 const AccessibilityObject* outer = objects[i];
2926 const AccessibilityObject* inner = objects[i - 1];
2927 // FIXME: unclear if we need LegacyIOSDocumentVisibleRect.
2928 const IntRect outerRect = i < levels ? snappedIntRect(outer->boundingBoxRect()) : outer->getScrollableAreaIfScrollable()->visibleContentRect(ScrollableArea::LegacyIOSDocumentVisibleRect);
2929 const IntRect innerRect = snappedIntRect(inner->isScrollView() ? inner->parentObject()->boundingBoxRect() : inner->boundingBoxRect());
2930
2931 if (!outerRect.intersects(innerRect)) {
2932 isOnscreen = false;
2933 break;
2934 }
2935 }
2936
2937 return isOnscreen;
2938}

2953
2954void AccessibilityObject::scrollToMakeVisibleWithSubFocus(const IntRect& subfocus) const
2955{
2956 // Search up the parent chain until we find the first one that's scrollable.
2957 AccessibilityObject* scrollParent = parentObject();
2958 ScrollableArea* scrollableArea;
2959 for (scrollableArea = nullptr;
2960 scrollParent && !(scrollableArea = scrollParent->getScrollableAreaIfScrollable());
2961 scrollParent = scrollParent->parentObject()) { }
2962 if (!scrollableArea)
2963 return;
2964
2965 LayoutRect objectRect = boundingBoxRect();
2966 IntPoint scrollPosition = scrollableArea->scrollPosition();
2967 // FIXME: unclear if we need LegacyIOSDocumentVisibleRect.
2968 IntRect scrollVisibleRect = scrollableArea->visibleContentRect(ScrollableArea::LegacyIOSDocumentVisibleRect);
2969
2970 if (!scrollParent->isScrollView()) {
2971 objectRect.moveBy(scrollPosition);
2972 objectRect.moveBy(-snappedIntRect(scrollParent->elementRect()).location());
2973 }
2974
2975 int desiredX = computeBestScrollOffset(
2976 scrollPosition.x(),
2977 objectRect.x() + subfocus.x(), objectRect.x() + subfocus.maxX(),
2978 objectRect.x(), objectRect.maxX(),
2979 0, scrollVisibleRect.width());
2980 int desiredY = computeBestScrollOffset(
2981 scrollPosition.y(),
2982 objectRect.y() + subfocus.y(), objectRect.y() + subfocus.maxY(),
2983 objectRect.y(), objectRect.maxY(),
2984 0, scrollVisibleRect.height());
2985
2986 scrollParent->scrollTo(IntPoint(desiredX, desiredY));
2987
2988 // Convert the subfocus into the coordinates of the scroll parent.
2989 IntRect newSubfocus = subfocus;
2990 IntRect newElementRect = snappedIntRect(elementRect());
2991 IntRect scrollParentRect = snappedIntRect(scrollParent->elementRect());
2992 newSubfocus.move(newElementRect.x(), newElementRect.y());
2993 newSubfocus.move(-scrollParentRect.x(), -scrollParentRect.y());
2994
2995 // Recursively make sure the scroll parent itself is visible.
2996 if (scrollParent->parentObject())
2997 scrollParent->scrollToMakeVisibleWithSubFocus(newSubfocus);
2998}
2999
3000void AccessibilityObject::scrollToGlobalPoint(const IntPoint& globalPoint) const
3001{
3002 // Search up the parent chain and create a vector of all scrollable parent objects
3003 // and ending with this object itself.
3004 Vector<const AccessibilityObject*> objects;
3005
3006 objects.append(this);
3007 for (AccessibilityObject* parentObject = this->parentObject(); parentObject; parentObject = parentObject->parentObject()) {
3008 if (parentObject->getScrollableAreaIfScrollable())
3009 objects.append(parentObject);
3010 }
3011
3012 objects.reverse();
3013
3014 // Start with the outermost scrollable (the main window) and try to scroll the
3015 // next innermost object to the given point.
3016 int offsetX = 0, offsetY = 0;
3017 IntPoint point = globalPoint;
3018 size_t levels = objects.size() - 1;
3019 for (size_t i = 0; i < levels; i++) {
3020 const AccessibilityObject* outer = objects[i];
3021 const AccessibilityObject* inner = objects[i + 1];
3022
3023 ScrollableArea* scrollableArea = outer->getScrollableAreaIfScrollable();
3024
3025 LayoutRect innerRect = inner->isScrollView() ? inner->parentObject()->boundingBoxRect() : inner->boundingBoxRect();
3026 LayoutRect objectRect = innerRect;
3027 IntPoint scrollPosition = scrollableArea->scrollPosition();
3028
3029 // Convert the object rect into local coordinates.
3030 objectRect.move(offsetX, offsetY);
3031 if (!outer->isScrollView())
3032 objectRect.move(scrollPosition.x(), scrollPosition.y());
3033
3034 int desiredX = computeBestScrollOffset(
3035 0,
3036 objectRect.x(), objectRect.maxX(),
3037 objectRect.x(), objectRect.maxX(),
3038 point.x(), point.x());
3039 int desiredY = computeBestScrollOffset(
3040 0,
3041 objectRect.y(), objectRect.maxY(),
3042 objectRect.y(), objectRect.maxY(),
3043 point.y(), point.y());
3044 outer->scrollTo(IntPoint(desiredX, desiredY));
3045
3046 if (outer->isScrollView() && !inner->isScrollView()) {
3047 // If outer object we just scrolled is a scroll view (main window or iframe) but the
3048 // inner object is not, keep track of the coordinate transformation to apply to
3049 // future nested calculations.
3050 scrollPosition = scrollableArea->scrollPosition();
3051 offsetX -= (scrollPosition.x() + point.x());
3052 offsetY -= (scrollPosition.y() + point.y());
3053 point.move(scrollPosition.x() - innerRect.x(),
3054 scrollPosition.y() - innerRect.y());
3055 } else if (inner->isScrollView()) {
3056 // Otherwise, if the inner object is a scroll view, reset the coordinate transformation.
3057 offsetX = 0;
3058 offsetY = 0;
3059 }
3060 }
3061}

3068 if ((scrollers.first = scrollers.second->getScrollableAreaIfScrollable()))
3069 break;
3070 }

3103
3104bool AccessibilityObject::scrollByPage(ScrollByPageDirection direction) const
3105{
3106 std::pair<ScrollableArea*, AccessibilityObject*> scrollers;
3107 scrollAreaAndAncestor(scrollers);
3108 ScrollableArea* scrollableArea = scrollers.first;
3109 AccessibilityObject* scrollParent = scrollers.second;
3110
3111 if (!scrollableArea)
3112 return false;
3113
3114 IntPoint scrollPosition = scrollableArea->scrollPosition();
3115 IntPoint newScrollPosition = scrollPosition;
3116 IntSize scrollSize = scrollableArea->contentsSize();
3117 IntRect scrollVisibleRect = scrollableArea->visibleContentRect(ScrollableArea::LegacyIOSDocumentVisibleRect);
3118 switch (direction) {
3119 case ScrollByPageDirection::Right: {
3120 int scrollAmount = scrollVisibleRect.size().width();
3121 int newX = scrollPosition.x() - scrollAmount;
3122 newScrollPosition.setX(std::max(newX, 0));
3123 break;
3124 }
3125 case ScrollByPageDirection::Left: {
3126 int scrollAmount = scrollVisibleRect.size().width();
3127 int newX = scrollAmount + scrollPosition.x();
3128 int maxX = scrollSize.width() - scrollAmount;
3129 newScrollPosition.setX(std::min(newX, maxX));
3130 break;
3131 }
3132 case ScrollByPageDirection::Up: {
3133 int scrollAmount = scrollVisibleRect.size().height();
3134 int newY = scrollPosition.y() - scrollAmount;
3135 newScrollPosition.setY(std::max(newY, 0));
3136 break;
3137 }
3138 case ScrollByPageDirection::Down: {
3139 int scrollAmount = scrollVisibleRect.size().height();
3140 int newY = scrollAmount + scrollPosition.y();
3141 int maxY = scrollSize.height() - scrollAmount;
3142 newScrollPosition.setY(std::min(newY, maxY));
3143 break;
3144 }
3145 }
3146
3147 if (newScrollPosition != scrollPosition) {
3148 scrollParent->scrollTo(newScrollPosition);
3149 document()->updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
3150 return true;
3151 }
3152
3153 return false;
3154}

3321 elements.append(element);
3322 }

3588void AccessibilityObject::setIsIgnoredFromParentDataForChild(AXCoreObject* child)
3589{

3594 child->clearIsIgnoredFromParentData();

3598 AccessibilityIsIgnoredFromParentData result = AccessibilityIsIgnoredFromParentData(this);
3599 if (!m_isIgnoredFromParentData.isNull()) {
3600 result.isAXHidden = (m_isIgnoredFromParentData.isAXHidden || equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(child->getAttribute(aria_hiddenAttr), "true")) && !child->isFocused();
3601 result.isPresentationalChildOfAriaRole = m_isIgnoredFromParentData.isPresentationalChildOfAriaRole || ariaRoleHasPresentationalChildren();
3602 result.isDescendantOfBarrenParent = m_isIgnoredFromParentData.isDescendantOfBarrenParent || !canHaveChildren();
3603 } else {

3637static bool isAccessibilityObjectSearchMatchAtIndex(AXCoreObject* axObject, AccessibilitySearchCriteria const& criteria, size_t index)
3638{
3639 switch (criteria.searchKeys[index]) {
3640 case AccessibilitySearchKey::AnyType:
3641 // The AccessibilitySearchKey::AnyType matches any non-null AccessibilityObject.
3642 return true;
3643 case AccessibilitySearchKey::Article:
3644 return axObject->roleValue() == AccessibilityRole::DocumentArticle;
3645 case AccessibilitySearchKey::BlockquoteSameLevel:
3646 return criteria.startObject
3647 && axObject->isBlockquote()
3648 && axObject->blockquoteLevel() == criteria.startObject->blockquoteLevel();
3649 case AccessibilitySearchKey::Blockquote:
3650 return axObject->isBlockquote();
3651 case AccessibilitySearchKey::BoldFont:
3652 return axObject->hasBoldFont();
3653 case AccessibilitySearchKey::Button:
3654 return axObject->isButton();
3655 case AccessibilitySearchKey::CheckBox:
3656 return axObject->isCheckbox();
3657 case AccessibilitySearchKey::Control:
3658 return axObject->isControl();
3659 case AccessibilitySearchKey::DifferentType:
3660 return criteria.startObject
3661 && axObject->roleValue() != criteria.startObject->roleValue();
3662 case AccessibilitySearchKey::FontChange:
3663 return criteria.startObject
3664 && !axObject->hasSameFont(*criteria.startObject);
3665 case AccessibilitySearchKey::FontColorChange:
3666 return criteria.startObject
3667 && !axObject->hasSameFontColor(*criteria.startObject);
3668 case AccessibilitySearchKey::Frame:
3669 return axObject->isWebArea();
3670 case AccessibilitySearchKey::Graphic:
3671 return axObject->isImage();
3672 case AccessibilitySearchKey::HeadingLevel1:
3673 return axObject->headingLevel() == 1;
3674 case AccessibilitySearchKey::HeadingLevel2:
3675 return axObject->headingLevel() == 2;
3676 case AccessibilitySearchKey::HeadingLevel3:
3677 return axObject->headingLevel() == 3;
3678 case AccessibilitySearchKey::HeadingLevel4:
3679 return axObject->headingLevel() == 4;
3680 case AccessibilitySearchKey::HeadingLevel5:
3681 return axObject->headingLevel() == 5;
3682 case AccessibilitySearchKey::HeadingLevel6:
3683 return axObject->headingLevel() == 6;
3684 case AccessibilitySearchKey::HeadingSameLevel:
3685 return criteria.startObject
3686 && axObject->isHeading()
3687 && axObject->headingLevel() == criteria.startObject->headingLevel();
3688 case AccessibilitySearchKey::Heading:
3689 return axObject->isHeading();
3690 case AccessibilitySearchKey::Highlighted:
3691 return axObject->hasHighlighting();
3692 case AccessibilitySearchKey::KeyboardFocusable:
3693 return axObject->isKeyboardFocusable();
3694 case AccessibilitySearchKey::ItalicFont:
3695 return axObject->hasItalicFont();
3696 case AccessibilitySearchKey::Landmark:
3697 return axObject->isLandmark();
3698 case AccessibilitySearchKey::Link: {
3699 bool isLink = axObject->isLink();
3700#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
3701 if (!isLink)
3702 isLink = axObject->isDescendantOfRole(AccessibilityRole::WebCoreLink);
3703#endif
3704 return isLink;
3705 }
3706 case AccessibilitySearchKey::List:
3707 return axObject->isList();
3708 case AccessibilitySearchKey::LiveRegion:
3709 return axObject->supportsLiveRegion();
3710 case AccessibilitySearchKey::MisspelledWord:
3711 return axObject->hasMisspelling();
3712 case AccessibilitySearchKey::Outline:
3713 return axObject->isTree();
3714 case AccessibilitySearchKey::PlainText:
3715 return axObject->hasPlainText();
3716 case AccessibilitySearchKey::RadioGroup:
3717 return axObject->isRadioGroup();
3718 case AccessibilitySearchKey::SameType:
3719 return criteria.startObject
3720 && axObject->roleValue() == criteria.startObject->roleValue();
3721 case AccessibilitySearchKey::StaticText:
3722 return axObject->isStaticText();
3723 case AccessibilitySearchKey::StyleChange:
3724 return criteria.startObject
3725 && !axObject->hasSameStyle(*criteria.startObject);
3726 case AccessibilitySearchKey::TableSameLevel:
3727 return criteria.startObject
3728 && axObject->isTable() && axObject->isExposable()
3729 && axObject->tableLevel() == criteria.startObject->tableLevel();
3730 case AccessibilitySearchKey::Table:
3731 return axObject->isTable() && axObject->isExposable();
3732 case AccessibilitySearchKey::TextField:
3733 return axObject->isTextControl();
3734 case AccessibilitySearchKey::Underline:
3735 return axObject->hasUnderline();
3736 case AccessibilitySearchKey::UnvisitedLink:
3737 return axObject->isUnvisited();
3738 case AccessibilitySearchKey::VisitedLink:
3739 return axObject->isVisited();
3740 default:
3741 return false;
3742 }
3743}

3745static bool isAccessibilityObjectSearchMatch(AXCoreObject* axObject, AccessibilitySearchCriteria const& criteria)
3746{
3747 if (!axObject)
3748 return false;
3749
3750 size_t length = criteria.searchKeys.size();
3751 for (size_t i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
3752 if (isAccessibilityObjectSearchMatchAtIndex(axObject, criteria, i)) {
3753 if (criteria.visibleOnly && !axObject->isOnScreen())
3754 return false;
3755 return true;
3756 }
3757 }
3758 return false;
3759}

3761static bool isAccessibilityTextSearchMatch(AXCoreObject* axObject, AccessibilitySearchCriteria const& criteria)
3762{
3763 if (!axObject)
3764 return false;
3765 return axObject->containsText(criteria.searchText);
3766}
